    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "At about 1430 hours, 22 May 1950, the attached (See Inclosure 1)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "\"photograph\" was turned over to Agent John F. Quinn, CID, New Orleans Port of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "Embarkation. The individual who turned this material over to Quinn told him",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "that he had purchased the \"photograph\" from one [REDACTED] for the sum of $1.00. He stated that he thought",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "this material \"should be placed in the hands of the Government\", as it was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "supposed to be pictures of \"flying saucers\" and \"a man from Mars in the United",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "States\". The \"man from Mars\" was pictured as being in the custody of two military",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "policemen.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "(B-2)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "The individual turning this material over to Quinn gave his name as",
      "status": "image_matched"
